Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
AutoInsight is an autonomous AI research agent that generates weekly fintech and Web3 industry research reports. It demonstrates a complete self-sustaining economic loop by earning money through micropayments and spending those earnings autonomously on data and AI services.
The primary goal is to showcase how AI agents can participate as real economic actors using the Locus ecosystem — earning via PayWithLocus Checkout SDK and spending via the Locus API catalog. This aligns perfectly with the Paygentic Week 1 track: "Using PayWithLocus to leverage our suite" and the hackathon theme "Hack An Agent That Makes YOU Money!".
1.2 Scope
AutoInsight will:

Generate high-quality ~500-word research reports on fintech/Web3 topics using Claude.
Offer a free preview (first ~100 words) and unlock the full report after a $0.50 USDC micropayment.
Autonomously use earnings stored in a Locus wallet to pay for data APIs from the Locus catalog.
Provide a transparent dashboard showing earnings, spends, wallet balance, and net profit.
Support hackathon demo flows (including a manual "Advance Week" trigger).

Out of scope (for hackathon MVP): Full production cron jobs, advanced ML model training, multi-user authentication beyond demo, or complex governance policies.
1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations

Locus: AI agent payment infrastructure (paywithlocus.com).
PayWithLocus Checkout SDK: Stripe-style checkout for accepting USDC payments into Locus wallets.
Locus API Catalog: Pay-per-use APIs (news, market data, search, etc.) that agents can autonomously purchase.
USDC: USD Coin (stablecoin used for micropayments).
Autonomous Loop: Earn (from readers) → Store in Locus wallet → Spend on Locus APIs → Generate better reports.

