2. Overall Description
2.1 Product Perspective
AutoInsight transforms traditional static research into a living, self-funding AI agent. Instead of relying on subscriptions or sponsorships, the agent earns directly from users and reinvests in its own intelligence using Locus tools.
2.2 Product Functions

Topic-based report generation (user-selected or autonomous).
Tiered content access (free preview + paid full report).
Micropayment processing via PayWithLocus.
Autonomous data acquisition and report regeneration.
Real-time financial dashboard with earn/spend transparency.
PDF export of reports.

2.3 User Classes and Characteristics

End Users / Readers: Fintech & Web3 enthusiasts, investors, developers, analysts — want quick, affordable insights.
Demo / Hackathon Judges: Need to see the full earn → spend → generate loop clearly.
Agent Owner (You): Manages the Locus wallet and spending policies.

2.4 Operating Environment

Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
Deployed on Vercel
Backend: Next.js API routes
Payments & APIs: Locus platform (USDC on supported chains)

2.5 Design and Implementation Constraints

Must use PayWithLocus Checkout SDK for payments.
Must integrate Locus API catalog for autonomous data spends.
Frontend: Next.js 15 + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
AI: Anthropic Claude (optionally via Locus)
No heavy external dependencies beyond listed stack.

2.6 Assumptions and Dependencies

Access to Locus beta credits and SDK.
Availability of relevant APIs in the Locus catalog (news, market data, search).
Claude API key (or Locus-routed equivalent).
USDC wallet funding for demo purposes.

3. Specific Requirements
3.1 Functional Requirements
3.1.1 User-Facing Features
FR1: Report Browsing & Preview

Users can select a topic/category (DeFi, RWA, Stablecoins, AI x Crypto, etc.) or let the agent choose a trending topic.
Display free preview: first ~100 words + engaging teaser.
"Unlock Full Report" button triggers PayWithLocus checkout for $0.50 USDC.

FR2: Payment & Content Unlock

Integrate PayWithLocus Checkout SDK for seamless $0.50 USDC payment.
On successful payment confirmation (via webhook/polling), instantly display the full 500-word report.
Include sources, key insights, and a simple data visualization (chart).

FR3: Report Generation

Use Claude to generate well-structured 500-word reports.
Incorporate fresh data obtained from paid Locus APIs.
Support PDF download of the full report.

FR4: Archive

Show list of past weekly reports with dates and topics.

3.1.2 Autonomous Agent Features (Core Winning Element)
FR5: Autonomous Economic Loop

Backend agent checks Locus wallet balance and recent earnings.
Autonomously selects 3–5 relevant data APIs from Locus catalog.
Pays for them using funds from the Locus wallet.
Feeds purchased data into Claude to generate the next report.
Logs every spend with details (e.g., "$0.04 on DeFi news API").

FR6: Demo Controls

Prominent "Advance to Next Week" button that triggers the full autonomous cycle (for hackathon judging).
Optional spending policy settings (e.g., max weekly budget).

3.1.3 Dashboard
FR7: Financial Transparency Dashboard

Total earnings from all micropayments.
Total spent on Locus APIs and AI calls (with breakdown).
Current Locus wallet balance.
Transaction history (earnings + spends).
Visual charts (earn vs spend over simulated weeks).
Agent status summary (e.g., "This week: spent $0.21, earned $4.50 → Net +$4.29").

3.2 Non-Functional Requirements

Performance: Report generation < 15 seconds after payment; dashboard loads < 2 seconds.
Usability: Clean, modern fintech aesthetic; mobile-responsive; intuitive flow.
Reliability: Graceful error handling for payment failures or API spend issues.
Security: Secure handling of payment confirmations; no sensitive keys exposed client-side.
Scalability: Designed for hackathon demo (not production scale).
Maintainability: Clean code with comments on all Locus integration points.
Look & Feel: Dark mode friendly, professional, trustworthy branding with "AutoInsight" logo.

3.3 External Interface Requirements

PayWithLocus Checkout SDK: Drop-in integration for checkout UI and payment confirmation.
Locus API Catalog: Authenticated calls for paid data endpoints (news, market data, etc.).
Claude API: Structured prompting for consistent report quality.
Recharts: For dashboard visualizations.
@react-pdf/renderer: For PDF export.

4. System Architecture

Frontend: Next.js 15 App Router + React components (pages: Home, Report Viewer, Dashboard).
Backend: Next.js API routes handling payments, agent logic, and data orchestration.
Data Flow:
User requests report → Preview shown.
Payment via PayWithLocus → Funds to project wallet.
Agent detects earnings → Pays Locus APIs → Fetches data.
Claude generates report using paid data.
Dashboard reflects updated earn/spend metrics.


5. Data Models (High-Level)

Report: { id, topic, date, previewText, fullContent, sources, chartData }
Transaction: { id, type (earn/spend), amount, description, timestamp, apiEndpoint? }
Wallet: { balance, totalEarned, totalSpent }

6. Future Enhancements (Post-Hackathon)

Real cron-based weekly generation.
Multi-topic subscriptions.
Advanced spending policies and agent governance.
Integration with more Locus tools (e.g., x402 payments, escrow).
